LogFile.FinalText: In many homes, you find a pet, and most people prefer either a dog or a cat. So far, the cute puppy beats the nice little kitten in the race for being Denmark's most popular pet. While the loyalty of the dog explains its big popularity, the numerous cat owners love the cat's independence. While the regular cat owner thinks that a dog is to non-independent and dirty, many dog owners perceive cats as lazy and unpersonal. Many pet owners choose a pet that reflects their own personality. When a big strong man buys a big strong dog, the dog's traits reinforces the dow owners ego. Vice versa, the feminine woman often perfer the beautiful and elegant cat. The dog and the cat normally get along without problems if they are used to each other. Often the dog owner and the cat owner are arguing more than the dog and the cat.
